= Quick Thin Pizza

Quickly-prepared pizza with a thin crust. Adapted from a recipe by PJ Hamel:
https://www.kingarthurbaking.com/recipes/super-fast-thin-crust-pizza-dough-recipe

#v(1em)

#columns(2)[
  == Equipment

  - Oven
  - Baking tray#footnote[~Cast iron preferred. A #url[baking steel] may also prove
      helpful. My tray has an area of 465cm#super[2] (72in#super[2]); adjust the recipe to
      compensate.]
  - Medium bowl
  - Stand mixer (optional) OR large bowl
  - Small towel, to cover above bowl

  *Yields 1 pizza.*

  #colbreak()

  == Ingredients

  === Dough
  - 150 g. (2/3 cup) water, warm
  - 5 g. (1/2 tbsp.) instant yeast
  - 240 g. (2 cups) all-purpose flour#footnote[~While you _can_ use bread flour, it will
      not work well, because this recipe is very thin.]
  - 3 grams (1/2 tsp.) salt
  - 4 grams (1 tsp.) baking powder
  - 40 grams (3 tbsp.) olive oil

  === Recommended Toppings

  - Tomato sauce
  - Shredded mozarrella
  - Turkey pepperoni
]

== Steps

#let sep = v(0.75em)
+ Mix dough together in this order: water & yeast; oil; remaining ingredients.
+ Let dough rest covered for 20 minutes. #sep
+ As dough continues resting, preheat oven to 225°C (450°F). Wait 10 minutes. #sep
+ Flatten dough into crust on baking tray. Crust should be 1/2 to 1 cm. tall.
+ Bake for 10-12 minutes or until cooked throughout. #sep
+ Add toppings to pizza crust.
+ Bake 6-8 minutes, or until cheese begins to brown. #sep
+ Let rest for 3 minutes before serving.
